MANDRILL 
Until recently, it was thought that mandrills  
belonged to the baboon family, and it was assumed  
that mandrills had a social structure similar to other  
members of this family. However, a recent DNA study  
showing that mandrills are neither baboons nor  
closely related to them, combined with new field  
research on the mandrill, has given us a very  
different picture of mandrill society. 
 
